!TITLE
FATHER ACT
!WORDS
  These days fathers are definitely taking a more active role in 
child-raising than they did a generation ago, but what exactly does 
that mean? A Child magazine survey compared percentages of fathers 
participating in the following parenting activities:
                                          Now          Then
     putting kids to bed    62%           16%
     changing diapers       53%            6%
     reading to kids        49%           15%
     bathing children       46%           24%
     feeding children       40%           12%
     helping with homework  30%           21%
     cleaning house         25%            8%
     washing dishes         44%           16%

   One area where fathers' involvement hasn't changed much is in 
administering discipline. Sixty-five percent of fathers today 
discipline their children, compared to 61% a generation ago.
   Nearly half (49%) of wives feel that their husbands pay more 
attention to their children than to them.  Men perceive it 
differently, however, since only 28% of fathers think they give the 
kids more attention than the wife.
     "Father act."  Leadership, Fall 1993.  Page 129.  Topic: 
FATHERS.  See also 8935 and 8835.
